PN,30907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773843069
OL,3,CScottish Parliament votes to reject
OL,4,Cbill to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FThe move followed the passage of
OL,7,Flegislation in the Isle of Man, where
OL,8,Fthe Tynwald became the first
OL,9,Fparliament in the British Isles to
OL,10,Fagree a framework for assisted dying
OL,11,Fin March last year.
OL,13,FIn Wales, the Senedd backed a
OL,14,FLegislative Consent Motion (LCM),
OL,15,Fwhich means the service could one day
OL,16,Fbe made available on the NHS.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773843069
OL,3,CScottish Parliament votes to reject
OL,4,Cbill to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FMeanwhile, more than 100 Labour MPs
OL,7,Fwrote to Prime Minister Sir Keir
OL,8,FStarmer, urging him to stop the House
OL,9,Fof Lords from blocking the assisted
OL,10,Fdying Bill in England and Wales.
OL,12,FIn total, over 150 MPs have signed the
OL,13,Fprivate letter addressed to Starmer,
OL,14,Fincluding parliamentarians from the
OL,15,FConservatives, Liberal Democrats,
OL,16,FGreens, Plaid Cymru and Reform UK.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
